(7, 5, '8', '7,8', 'Because anticipation is part of the experience.', 'We have a variety of delicious drink creations available for your enjoyment.  Bring a friend and relax by our fireplace!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 14:41:29', '2021-06-25 14:41:29', 0, ''),
(9, 5, '13', '5', 'Your taste buds will love you forever and forever and then some...', 'It really is famous', 'Nada', 1, '2021-07-15', '2021-07-15', 1, '2021-07-15 18:19:13', '2021-07-15 18:19:13', 0, ''),
(11, 5, '18', '17', 'Beef', '4th Line Cattle Co. is family owned and operated in Hillsburgh Ontario. Providing locally raised, Grass fed, hormone Free quality Longhorn Meat.\n\n100% Longhorn meat, roasts, steaks, ground beef and hamburger patties.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:56:44', '2021-04-16 05:56:44', 0, ''),
(12, 5, '22', '', 'We look forward to seeing you soon!', 'Food you love...farmers you know. Come taste the best of the region and chat with our friendly growers and producers in our spacious open air pavilion.\n\nFully accessible facility. Free parking and an ATM available on-site.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:54', '2021-04-16 06:07:54', 0, ''),
(13, 5, '23', '', 'Looking forward to seeing you soon!', 'When people come to the Elora Farmers\' Market, they not only find great local foods, treats and artisanal products, they find each other too! The market is a true community hub and our customers\' energy is what makes the market so special.\n\nCome on out and meet the people who grow your food!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-13', '2021-04-13', 1, '2021-04-13 12:00:39', '2021-04-13 12:00:39', 0, ''),
(14, 5, '24', '', 'Come and visit us!', 'Delicious and local! Local food, fresh ideas in the Town of Erin. One stop destination!\n\nRain or shine.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:00:31', '2021-04-16 06:00:31', 0, ''),
(15, 5, '25', '', ' Enjoy some fresh local food!', 'One of Guelph’s oldest and well-loved community spaces offers fresh local food, artisanal products and a friendly, welcoming atmosphere year round. Guelph Farmers’ Market continues a tradition of pride and community building supporting the local economy, sustainability and entrepreneurship.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-13', '2021-04-13', 1, '2021-04-13 11:37:13', '2021-04-13 11:37:13', 0, ''),
(16, 5, '26', '', 'Come and connect with us', 'Located at the Palmerston Railway Heritage Museum.\n\n\"Fresh Local Real\" - featuring 100% locally grown/produced products!\n\nCome connect with community at the Minto Farmers\' Market!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-09-13', '2021-09-13', 1, '2021-09-13 16:20:48', '2021-09-13 16:20:48', 0, ''),
(17, 5, '27', '', 'Behind Rockmosa Community Centre', 'The Rockwood Farmers\' Market offers a large assortment of fresh produce, local meats and cheeses, prepared and frozen meals, local artisans as well as youth vendors.\n\nOur market is a unique community centric, family oriented place to visit each week. Offering live music, fresh foods for dinner and many kids activities.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-09-13', '2021-09-13', 1, '2021-09-13 16:21:54', '2021-09-13 16:21:54', 0, ''),
(18, 5, '28', '', 'We the North!', 'Located at Victory Community Centre.\n\nBuy top quality farm fresh products including produce, baked goods, preserves and handcrafted items directly from the producers while enjoying the atmosphere of Wellington North\'s Culture.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-09-13', '2021-09-13', 1, '2021-09-13 16:23:18', '2021-09-13 16:23:18', 0, ''),
(19, 5, '29', '', 'Beef, chicken, pork, lamb and eggs.', 'We are a family run farm raising sustainable, pasture raised and free range animals.\n\nOur products include pasture raised and grain finished beef, pasture raised chicken, pasture raised pork, pasture raised lamb, and free range eggs.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:57:10', '2021-04-16 05:57:10', 0, ''),
(20, 5, '30', '', 'Sheep dairy products, sheep gelato, lamb, poultry, wool', 'We are a pasture based sheep farm. From our flock of mixed dairy and fibre sheep we produce gelato and other seasonal dairy products. We produce and sell grass fed lamb from late summer through the winter. We process our wool and make felted home decor items.\n\nAll of our products are available from our farm store, or from weekly farmers\' markets:\n\nElora Farmers\' Market\nDufferin Grove Market\nMust Taste Item: Chocolate sheep milk gelato!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:08', '2021-04-16 06:07:08', 0, ''),
(21, 5, '31', '', 'Loose leaf herbal tea', 'We grow the ingredients on chemical-free land for our herbal tea blends just outside of Guelph, ON. Using permaculture and organic growing techniques, our herbs have been helping humans feel good since 2008.\n\nWe offer 5 loose leaf herbal tea blends, as well as some seasonal single herb teas.\n\nYou can order online or find our products at retail locations in Guelph and Kitchener-Waterloo.\n\nMust Taste: Nervina Herbal Tea', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:33', '2021-04-16 06:04:33', 0, ''),
(22, 5, '32', '', 'Arthur, Wellington North Township', 'Arthur Greenhouses, Nursery and Market Garden is a horticulture farm just east of Arthur. Owner Patrick is the 15th generation of farmers, his family farms since 1510 in Belgium and the south of Holland. He is the first in his family who farms in Canada. Together with his wife Joanna, who is the 5th generation of vegetable and flower grower, and their two teenagers.\n\nPatrick and Joanna farm with the same values as their grandparents and great grandparents. They collect water from the roof of all the buildings and reuse it in the greenhouses and in the fields. No pesticides are used in the greenhouses nor in the fields. Patrick and Joanna are passionate growers and love nature.\n\nThey offer a huge range of vegetables from their field; from beans to zucchini, fresh strawberries in season, sweet corn in season (not sprayed and non-GMO), potted herbs, fruit shrubs and fruit trees.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:56:09', '2021-04-16 05:56:09', 0, ''),
(23, 5, '33', '', 'Ontario honey, Beeswax Candles, Soap/Shampoo Bars, Lip Balm, Bug Balm and Ontario Native Plant and trees.', 'We are a small family-run farm producing honey, and a native and Carolinian nursery located in Puslinch.\n\nProducts we offer are honey, creamed honey, beeswax soaps and lip balms, Native and Carolinian trees, shrubs and wildflowers', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:43', '2021-04-16 06:05:43', 0, ''),
(24, 5, '34', '', 'Meats, baking, local products', 'Big John\'s Country Market features products farm grown Beef, Pork, Lamb, Produce, Maple Syrup. The market also carries fresh baking, and locally made goods and beverages.\n\nFind them at the Wellington North Farmers’ Market every Friday during the season and on the Spring Rural Romp. They are proud members of The Butter Tart Trail. Vegetables are Available In-Season 24/7 Self Serve.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:15', '2021-04-16 06:05:15', 0, ''),
(25, 5, '35', '', 'Bison Meat', 'Black Powder Bison Co. is raising an all natural, grass fed Bison herd. We provide direct to consumer Bison cuts from our farm store.\n\nEnjoy grass fed bison burgers, sausages, steaks and marrow bones.\n\nYou can also find our products at Top Market Meats and Mosborough Country Market.\n\nMust Taste Item: 100% natural Bison Sausages', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:58:27', '2021-04-16 05:58:27', 0, ''),
(26, 5, '36', '', 'Alpacas and alpaca products, lavender, honey', 'Modern eco-friendly farm specializing in alpacas, lavender and honey. Providing luxury and wholesome products that are simply better for you, them and us.\n\nFarm visits must be reserved online at www.braeridgefarm.com/events.\n\nMust Taste Items: Music Hardneck Garlic, Lavender Honey', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:55:48', '2021-04-16 05:55:48', 0, ''),
(27, 5, '37', '', 'Produce, flower planters', 'Buds and Blossoms Farm grows produce, perennials and flowers. Also creates various floral arrangements for on a table or for outdoor planters.\n\nHere are a few of our offerings: garlic, beets, carrots, potatoes, peppers, tomatoes, Spanish Onions, cooking onions, leek, Kale, Broccoli, Gladiolas, Zinnia\'s, Snapdragons, Sunflowers Pumpkins, Squash, Cauliflower, Sweet Potatoes, Corn, mini straw bales .', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:21', '2021-04-16 06:06:21', 0, ''),
(28, 5, '38', '', 'Dahila tubers', 'On the farm you can pick your own strawberries, raspberries, and pumpkins. Also to be found at their farm gate stall are: asparagus, potatoes, beets, carrots, squash, pumpkins, tomatoes, beans, pea\'s, flowers, honey, and jam just to name a few.\n\nCheck their facebook page during growing season for daily updates.\n\nPlease note it is cash sales only, and no pets please.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:01:20', '2021-04-16 06:01:20', 0, ''),
(29, 5, '39', '', 'Chicken and chicken products', 'We are a small family farm growing Farm Fresh Chicken through the Artisinal Chicken Program offered by the Chicken Farmer\'s of Ontario.\n\nWe offer Farm Fresh Chicken; Whole Roasting Chicken, Chicken Cuts and Eggs.\n\nMust Taste Item: Fresh, Whole Roasting Chicken', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:59:25', '2021-04-16 05:59:25', 0, ''),
(30, 5, '40', '', 'Honey', 'Cedarwood Honey is a family-run beekeeping operation that brings over 20 years worth of beekeeping experience to the Harriston area. Our business focus is to provide 100% local Ontario honey to our customers.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:00', '2021-04-16 06:04:00', 0, ''),
(31, 5, '41', '', 'Closed for the season.', 'Quality trees and wreaths. Free Kids\' Activity Area. Free Nature Trail with activity stations. Complimentary cider, candy canes and kids\' Puzzle Page. Beautiful Gift Shop. Dog Friendly (must be leashed).\n\nThey sell Cut-Your-Own Christmas trees including Balsam Fir, White Spruce and Scotch Pine, Pre-Cut Christmas trees including Fraser Fir and Balsam Fir, Greenery, and tree stands.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:59:48', '2021-04-16 05:59:48', 0, ''),
(32, 5, '42', '', 'Halal chicken, free range eggs, vegetables and maple syrup', 'Chicken Thika is a family-run farm that provides halal, organic, fresh and local poultry to Dufferin, Wellington, Bruce and Grey Counties in Ontario.\n\nWe are Certified Organic and offer halal chicken, free range eggs, vegetables and maple syrup. Our maple syrup is sourced locally and we continue to look for partnership opportunities with local farms to table to bring the best quality and variety to our clients at the farm gate.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:45', '2021-04-16 06:03:45', 0, ''),
(33, 5, '43', '', 'Erin, Town of Erin', 'Our mission is to produce delicious grass-fed beef for our local market. We raise our beef naturally without the use of hormones or antibiotics, in an environmentally sound manner. Open year round, welcome anytim ebut best to call ahead.\n\nTexas Longhorn beef. Sides, wuarters, boxesw and individual cuts available.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:25', '2021-04-16 06:02:25', 0, ''),
(34, 5, '44', '', 'Lamb meat, yarn, wool, fibre products', 'Located in southern Mapleton Township, Ryan and Romy Schill and family keep a flock of over 200 ewes. All lambs are raised on their family farm from birth and are grain finished resulting in a mild and tender meat. The soil types and climate also allow the Schill Family to grow a large variety of crops. Corn, hay (legumes and grasses), grains, pasture, soybeans, veggies, fruits, the possibilities are endless! There is no shortage of any type of crop. Being able to store and feed our quality feeds year round also allows us to have lambs born year round providing you the most delicious lamb.\n\nWe offer a variety of cuts, 1/4 or 1/2 lamb meat boxes or whole lambs butchered to your specifications. In addition to meat, they offer sheep skins, fibre products and yarn and wool processed at the Grand Valley Fibre Company close to Arthur.\n\nAlso be sure to check out our Revolution Wool Company website, where you\'ll find a large variety of handmade and ready to wear items and gifts made from 10% pure local wool:  www.revolutionwoolco.com', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-05-05', '2021-05-05', 1, '2021-05-05 11:46:49', '2021-05-05 11:46:49', 0, ''),
(35, 5, '45', '', 'Fergus, Centre Wellington Township Honey', 'Coneybeare Honey is a third generation honey production and beekeeping operation that first started in 1925. We have 725 hives in Wellington and Grey counties and focus on honey production, crop pollination and queen breeding. We can supply customer orders from 325g to filling barrels and totes for commercial orders. All of our honey is 100% natural, made by the bees.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:43', '2021-04-16 06:02:43', 0, ''),
(36, 5, '46', '', 'NOTE:  Currently not operating', 'Conroy\'s Crops is a small vegetable farm providing farmshares and flowershares to Guelph families. We are not certified organic but follow organic principals.\n\nCSA Pick-up locations can be found at:\n\n53 Munroe Crescent, Guelph (South End) Tuesday 5:00 pm-7:00 pm\n146 Metcalfe Street, Guelph (North End) Wednesday 4:00 pm-6:00 pm', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:38', '2021-04-16 06:05:38', 0, ''),
(37, 5, '47', '', 'Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'We specialize in growing herbs and world vegetables. An herb is mainly a title lumped to a variety of plants that have properties that are of benefit for animals or other plants. Produce grown includes world crops and recognized special varieties.\n\nMust Taste Item: Pickled Okra', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:14', '2021-04-16 06:07:14', 0, ''),
(38, 5, '48', '', 'Guelph, Guelph Eramosa Township', 'Beautiful rolling country farm right on the highway outside of the village of Eramosa. We offer a diverse selection 25-30 different seasonal vegetables and strawberries. Popular items include green and yellow beans, tomatoes, carrots, beets, snap peas and garlic.\n\nWe aim to be sustainable and as close to 0 carbon footprint as possible, with a straw-bale house and naturally managed gardens. We follow Coleman\'s philosophy of \"feed the soil\" that builds healthy topsoil and contributes to carbon capture. Step back in time to experience our \"old-school\" approach of marketing and interacting with customers. Free range chickens and some friendly pygmy goats add to the charm.\n\nFind our products at the Erin Farmers\' Market, enjoy our CSA program, and we provide produce drop-offs in Waterloo.\n\nMust Taste Item: French cut green beans', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:27', '2021-04-16 06:03:27', 0, ''),
(39, 5, '49', '', 'Beef boxes', 'As stewards of the land we are amazed by the regenerative powers of pastures and cattle. We raised 100 head of cattle in our 100 acres of pasture. We strive to be leaders in animal husbandry and welfare. We consider the well being of our animals, our environment, our business and our health in our production decisions. We think you will easily notice our level of care in the quality of products we offer.\n\nThe breed of cattle we raise is Speckle Park which is known for its ability to finish on pastures and for its meat tendernes and flavour. We offer monthly feature boxes as well as custom orders of our pasture raised beef.\n\nOpen by appointment.\n\nMust Taste Item: Our Wellington County Breakfast Steaks', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:56:54', '2021-04-16 05:56:54', 0, ''),
(40, 5, '50', '', 'Beef products, summer sausage, pepperettes, jerky, maple syrup, apple cider.', 'We are a family farm that raise and produce quality products to feed your family.\n\nBeef products include steaks, roasts, stewing beef, ground beef, soup bones, hamburgers, sausage, etc.\n\nSummer Sausage, Pepperettes, Jerky\n\nMaple Syrup\n\nApple Cider', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:57:02', '2021-04-16 05:57:02', 0, ''),
(41, 5, '51', '', 'Moorefield, Mapleton Township Beef', 'Ell-Crest Farms is located on County Rd 8 between Drayton and Palmerston, 1 Mile North-East of Moorefield. Previously a dairy farm, Paul and Pam Ellis know all about what it takes to raise healthy, premium cattle.\n\n*Cash or Cheque only. Currently taking phone orders and outside pick-up is available.\n\nYou will find every kind of beef from hamburgers, roasts, steaks, stewing beef, and pepperettes. Their beef is home grown, butchered and inspected by Elora Road Meats in Mildmay.\n\nMust Taste Item: 100% Beef Extra Lean Hamburgers', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:32', '2021-04-16 06:05:32', 0, ''),
(42, 5, '52', '', 'Fresh cut trees available, u-cut sold out for the season.', 'Elliott Tree Farm is a circa 1890 family Christmas tree farm located just 6km north of the scenic village of Hillsburgh. We specialize in Ontario’s Best fresh cut Fir and Blue Spruce Christmas trees, cut your own Spruce and Pine Christmas trees and farm fresh hand made wreaths.\n\nWe also offer a selection of Winter-Christmas-Holiday planters, greens, tree stands and country gifts.\n\nCut your own Christmas trees\nFresh cut Christmas trees\nFresh made wreaths\nGreenery and birch\nPlanters\nGifts and crafts\nPure maple syrup\nPure honey\nMust Taste Item: Hot chocolate bar', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:58', '2021-04-16 06:02:58', 0, ''),
(43, 5, '53', '', 'Sold out for the season', 'Evergreen Tree Farm is located just 8 km north of Guelph on Wellington Road 22. Bring the family to enjoy a truly unforgettable day in the country. You may choose and cut your own Christmas tree, purchase from a selection of fresh cut trees or simply come out and browse through the gift shop.\n\nWe feature the work of local artisans with arts, crafts, bath products, jewelry, scarves, chocolate, candy and preserves in our warm barn gift shop. Enjoy our outdoor firepits where families are invited to roast marshmallows, relax and enjoy the warmth. We have fresh wreaths, green arrangements, birch poles and urn filler. Use of sleighs, saws, shaking/baling and twine are all included in the cost of the tree.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:21', '2021-04-16 06:07:21', 0, ''),
(44, 5, '54', '', 'Honey, soap', 'Homegrown and Handcrafted.\n\nWe are an urban farm on 2 acres with an orchard, veggie garden, two green houses, rabbits and hens.\n\nOffering eggs, veggies, fruit, herbs, handcrafted cold processed soap, raw honey, and small batch preserves. Chemical Free.\n\nOpen year round by appointment. You can also find us as an occasional vendor at the Elora Farmers\' Market!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:05', '2021-04-16 06:04:05', 0, ''),
(45, 5, '55', '', 'Baked goods for dietary needs (vegan, keto, gluten free) breads and baked goods, and beef.', 'Seasonal produce, organic grass fed beef, organic chicken and pork, baked goods through the Saturday Farmers\' Market in Guelph; a vegetable CSA (Community Supported Agriculture)', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:56:27', '2021-04-16 05:56:27', 0, ''),
(46, 5, '56', '', 'Live micro greens', 'We are a 100 acre farm just north of Rockwood, Ontario.\n\nWe offer live microgreens sold in sugarcane clamshells or by the tray (all microgreens are grown from Canadian Certified Organic and Non GMO Seeds). Sold in organic hemp fiber no soil. We also grow Arugula, Broccoli, Cabbage, Mustard-Oriental Wasabi, Peas, Radish-Kaiware, and Garlic.\n\nYou can find us at the Guelph Farmers\' Market, Rockwood Farmers\' Market, and Lakeview Farmers\' Market. Farm pick-up by appointment only.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:28', '2021-04-16 06:04:28', 0, ''),
(47, 5, '57', '', 'Grocery items, flowers, seedlings', 'We are a family business, producing and retailing fresh local produce in season, we also carry a variety of frozen meats, homemade baking and preserves.\n\nWe are passionate about providing our local community with fresh, local, healthy foods at affordable prices.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:21', '2021-04-16 06:03:21', 0, ''),
(48, 5, '58', '', 'Vegetables, preserves', 'Market garden, berries and orchard.\n\nOffering strawberries, Raspberries, vegetables potatoes orchard fruit (apples, cherries), garlic.\n\nPreserves (jams and jellies)\n\nSeasonal, call ahead for availability. No Sunday Sales.\n\nVisit us at the Minto Farmers’ Market or our Farm Gate.\n\nMust Taste Item: Raspberries', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:43', '2021-04-16 06:07:43', 0, ''),
(49, 5, '104', '', 'Greens', 'GoodLeaf Farms is a new, state-of-the-art, fully automated vertical farming facility revolutionizing how clean, fresh, local greens are being grown in Canada and around the world. As the leader in the vertical farming movement, we have set the bar high in in terms of safety, quality and freshness.\n\nFind us in: Loblaw, Sobeys, Longo\'s, J.E. Russell (in the food terminal) and Fresh Start (wholesale distributor).\n\nComing late summer 2019!\n\nMust Taste Item: Micro Spicy Mustard Medley', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:04', '2021-04-16 06:03:04', 0, ''),
(50, 5, '59', '', 'Greens Contactless pickup at their modular farm.', 'GR365N (Green 365) produces farm to table leafy greens grown in a new state of the art hydroponic farm. We believe that freshness and optimal nutrition is not something that should be compromised. We grow without using harmful pesticides or herbicides. Our goal is to help reduce the emission of greenhouse gases that are often attributed to the transportation of our food that is often over 2,500 km. While ensuring the freshest food to our customers.\n\nWe are currently offering fresh kale (Starbor and Tuscan), fresh herbs and will be adding microgreens to our product list. Our Products are often changing based on demand so please feel free to reach out at info@gr365n.com for order inquiries.\n\nWe also provide home hydroponic installation, support and maintenance as part of our services. Our purpose is to help individuals grow fresh food at home... anytime.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:10', '2021-04-16 06:03:10', 0, ''),
(51, 5, '60', '', 'Eggs, Garlic/Garlic Scapes, Turnips, Sweet Potatoes, Beans, Peas, Brussel Sprouts, Tomatoes.', 'We are a new spray free permaculture farm in Northeast Puslinch.\n\nWe offer Garlic Scapes and Garlic, Turnips, Sweet Potatoes, Beans, Peas, Brussel Sprouts, Tomatoes.  Fruit and Nuts (future).  Eggs.\n\nMust Taste Item: Fermented Black Garlic', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:10', '2021-04-16 06:02:10', 0, ''),
(52, 5, '61', '', 'Alpaca wool and fibre products', 'Harmony Meadows Alpaca is a small farm in Wellington County that focuses on breeding high quality animals for the purpose of manufacturing quality fibre goods and improving the Canadian herd.\n\nFibre from these beautiful animals is sold as raw fleece or can be processed into everything from yarns to socks to fine clothing. Even the lower quality fibre can be used in duvets and other felted goods.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:55:18', '2021-04-16 05:55:18', 0, ''),
(53, 5, '62', '', 'Hard cider, maple syrup and beef', '\nSet amidst the rolling hills and meandering rivers near the Village of Erin, Heartwood Farm and Cidery is a diverse 42-acre ecosystem of mixed pasture, fruit and nut orchards, woods and wetlands. We\'re dedicated to regenerative agriculture practices that produce healthy soils, sustainable water and nutrient cycles, contented animals, wholesome food for our community and valuable habitat for wildlife and pollinators.\n\nUsing these practices we are able to connect farm, food and craft beverage to the simple wonders of life. Our small batch ciders are inspired by what grows on our farm and in our community and the stories that weave people and place together. Sign up for one of our unique on-farm experiences and join the conversation by heading to www.heartwoodfarm.ca\n\nOur products can also be found at:\n\nGuelph Farmers\' Market\nErin Farmers\' Market\nSorauren Farmers\' Market\nand select restaurants and bars in Guelph and Toronto\nMust Taste Item: Farm-produced craft apple ciders including blends inspired by what grows in our forests, gardens and orchards.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:51', '2021-04-16 06:03:51', 0, ''),
(54, 5, '63', '', 'Fergus, Centre Wellington Township Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'Hoppy Fields Farm is a small, organically run vegetable farm located just outside of Fergus, Ontario. We chose the name Hoppy Fields Farm because a large part of the property is a forest/wetland ecosystem, home to an incredible amount of living things, including more frogs and toads than we could ever hope to count!\n\nOur goal is to produce the most nutritious and delicious food possible, and make it accessible for as many members of our community as we can. We also strive to practice regenerative farming techniques, building healthy soils and fostering systems that promote life in all it\'s diversity.\n\nFor more information about the farm and our CSA program click here https://www.hoppyfieldsfarm.com/potowski-av/\n\nIf you are interested in becoming a volunteer CSA member click here https://www.hoppyfieldsfarm.com/volunteer-csa-share/', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:48', '2021-04-16 06:02:48', 0, ''),
(55, 5, '64', '', 'Meats', 'Traditionally raised Heritage Breeds. No antibiotics, hormones or GMO crops. Delivery available, see website for details and to view our online store.\n\nMust Taste Item: 25 lbs of assorted cuts of frozen beef or pork', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:01', '2021-04-16 06:05:01', 0, ''),
(56, 5, '65', '', 'Guelph, Guelph Eramosa TownshipSign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'Ignatius Farm grows organic vegetables, strawberries, and a variety of field crops.\n\nThe Farm bridges the urban with rural, and invites the surrounding community to enjoy and get involved in their local farm.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:39', '2021-04-16 06:03:39', 0, ''),
(57, 5, '66', '', 'Roasted nuts', 'Homemade nuts and granolas using fruit from our orchard and Ontario\'s finest maple syrup.\n\nOntario\'s #1 Nut Grower - Artisan Nut Producer', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:45', '2021-04-16 06:06:45', 0, ''),
(58, 5, '67', '', 'Closed for the season', 'We have the best super sweet corn, GMO free. Farm to table &ndash; fresh fruit and vegetables grown locally and available to you. Place your order for upcoming events.\n\nAll Ontario grown, from our farm to your family.\n\nCall us to reserve your corn, fruit and vegetables. We sell out fast! Place your orders for the canning season, bushels of tomatoes, pickling cucumbers, etc.\n\nFollow us on Facebook for what’s in season.\n\nMUST TASTE ITEM: Our freshly picked SUPER SWEET CORN', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:59:36', '2021-04-16 05:59:36', 0, ''),
(59, 5, '68', '', 'Fresh checken meat, seasonal fruits and vegetables, pick your own berries, maple syrup, Spring greenhouse nursery plants, Fall pumpkin patch, seasonal decor', 'We are a small, but growing, family run farm offering fresh and frozen chicken in the centre of Wellington County. Situated just North of Belwood Lake, we have a lovely 10 acres that provides our farming space as well as a large outdoor play area for children of all ages, and forested areas with beautiful hiking and an up close view of some nearby windmills.\n\nSpecializing in fresh chicken meat, seasonal fruits and vegetables, pick your own berries, Spring greenhouse nursery plants, Fall pumpkin patch, roadside shopping, a huge playzone for kids, and a few other small endeavors like fresh Maple syrup and seasonal décor! Property available for outdoor photoshoots.\n\nMust Taste: Farm fresh chicken, GMO free grain fed, hormone and antibiotic free.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:53', '2021-04-16 06:02:53', 0, ''),
(60, 5, '69', '', 'Alma, Mapleton Township', 'Come and visit the Kabbespatch and learn about life on a family farm.  Say hello to our baby chicks, ducklings and pigs and collect farm fresh eggs.  Try some sausage and browse our farm store for fresh eggs and chicken, pork, or guinea fowl.\n\nAll of our meat is government inspected, and ready to serve your family tonight.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-30', '2021-06-30', 1, '2021-06-30 10:22:40', '2021-06-30 10:22:40', 0, ''),
(61, 5, '70', '', 'Lentils', 'Ontario\'s ONLY lentil growers. Grown sustainably on our family farm just outside of Elora, Ontario.\n\nOur family has been farming for more than 150 years. We grow corn, soybeans, wheat, hay and now green lentils! The Austin and Ferrier families work hard each and every year to produce healthy and nutritious crops to be used locally or exported worldwide. Our crops are grown sustainably to ensure that we leave our land better than we found it.\n\nOur offerings include lentils as well as all-natural whole lentil flour. Wholesale or pre-order only. Large Green Lentils available in 2 cup bags for retail sales up to 55lb bulk bags. Whole Lentil Flour available in 1lb bags for retail sales up to 44lb bulk bags.\n\nWe are sold at numerous local farm markets, specialty stores, as well as used in local restaurants.\n\nMust Taste Item: We highly suggest making our Lau-tea-da Lentil Hummus!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:22', '2021-04-16 06:04:22', 0, ''),
(62, 5, '71', '', 'Elora, Centre Wellington Township Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'We are a small organic vegetable farm, offering CSA shares and are full time vendors at the Elora Farmers\' Market.\n\nMust Taste Item: Garlic', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:18', '2021-04-16 06:02:18', 0, ''),
