(64, 5, '73', '', 'Maples syrup, maple taffy cones', 'We are a family owned business. We make our own Maple Syrup, with 3000 trees tapped locally. We pride ourselves on our quality. Our products are available at our farm, near Drayton, Ontario.\n\nWe offer four types of maple syrup available in different sizes. \n\nGolden - Ontario grate A for mild taste\nAmber - Ontario grade A for rich taste.\nDark - Ontario grade A for robust taste.\nVery Dark - Ontario grade A for very robust taste.\nour production facility is CFIA inspected. For large orders, please contact us directly, via email or phone.\n\nMust Taste: maple syrup', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:48', '2021-04-16 06:04:48', 0, ''),
(65, 5, '74', '', 'Pastured meats and eggs, maple syrup and honey.', 'Building our family farm to provide our community with healthy, nutritious pasture raised meats, eggs and maple syrup. We use regenerative practices to ensure we’re not only raising top quality meat, under the best care, but also improving the soil and land while doing it.\n\nMust Taste Item: heritage breed bacon!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:08', '2021-04-16 06:06:08', 0, ''),
(66, 5, '75', '', 'Water buffalo meat', 'Majestic Water Buffalo breeds and raises Water Buffalo for meat in Erin Township, Ontario, Canada. The animals are locally raised to high standards of animal welfare on our 97 acre farm alongside our Angus Cattle.\n\nWater Buffalo Meat is low in fat, calories and cholesterol and has a mild flavour, and high digestibility.\n\nOpen year round. Pick-up at farm by appointment.\n\nYou can also find us at:\n\nElora Farmers\' Market\nErin Farmers\' Market\nGuelph Farmers\' Market\nFrapers Fresh Foods\nTop Market Meats\nMust Taste Item: Water Buffalo Meat', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:49', '2021-04-16 06:07:49', 0, ''),
(67, 5, '76', '', 'Ice cream, meats', 'Please note our farm is currently closed to the public. We have launched a new website for delivery of our products, please visit www.mapletonsorganicdelivered.com or email mapletonsdelivered@gmail.com. Delivery area includes Town of Minto, Mapleton Township, Arthur, Fergus/Elora, Elmira, and Kitchener/ Waterloo.\n\nMapleton’s Organic provides healthy, local, and environmentally sustainable products produced in their on-farm dairy.  It is a core belief of Mapleton’s that people should have the opportunity to see their food being produced up close, so guests and visitors are welcome!\n\nAll Mapleton\'s products (ice cream, frozen yogurt and fresh yogurt) are produced using milk from the herd of 70 dairy cows.\n\nThe Mapleton\'s farm is home to many other animals: young dairy animals; pigs for organic pork; free-range chickens and turkeys are added to the mix each summer.\n\nCome into the farm store to see our selection of frozen meats, and take home a tub of our delicious ice cream. Stay for a scoop or two, or have lunch at our small cafe, serving sandwiches made with ingredients right off the farm (in season), homemade soup and more!\n\nMUST TASTE ITEM: Our Dandelion Ice', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:10', '2021-04-16 06:04:10', 0, ''),
(68, 5, '77', '', 'Grocery items, baking, produce, meats and more', 'Quality fresh from the farm!\n\nExperience the charismatic country charm of our family run business.\n\nHomegrown sweet corn, pumpkins, local produce, from scratch baking and much more.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:15', '2021-04-16 06:03:15', 0, ''),
(69, 5, '78', '', 'Pasture pork, chicken, turkey, beef, eggs and seasonal honey, apple cider, elderberries, rhubarb and more.', 'We are a small farm between Arthur and Grand Valley raising pasture pork, chicken, turkey, and beef. We offer free range eggs and seasonal items such as honey, apple cider, elderberries, rhubarb and much more! We are passionate about using sustainable and regenerative farming practices to provide local food for our community.\n\nMust Taste: Free Range Eggs - customers rave about the buttery yolks', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:01', '2021-04-16 06:06:01', 0, ''),
(70, 5, '79', '', 'Alpaca wool and fibre products, alpaca meat', 'The first two alpacas joined the 24-acre Poot family farm in 2004 and since then Peter and Suelaine have grown their farm to produce both clothing fibres and alpaca meat. As a result, Pootcorners is a sustainable, no-waste practice producing beautiful, natural coloured Alpaca hides as well as clothing and other soft fibre products.\n\nThe Alpaca meat is lean and tasty. Pepperettes and summer sausage are ready to travel and a variety of frozen cuts from tenderloins, ribs, chops and ground meat are available.\n\nYou can find Pootcorner\'s products at local fairs, farmers\' markets and craft shows during the summer and fall months. You can also visit the farm year-round in Palmerston Ontario; call ahead for store hours.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:55:38', '2021-04-16 05:55:38', 0, ''),
(71, 5, '80', '', 'Beef, or sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', '\nA small mixed farm using organic and sustainable practices to grow vegetables and pastured meats.\n\nOffering:\n\nGrass Finished Beef\nPastured Pork\nFree Range Eggs\nPastured Rabbit\nVegetables\nCSA\nCut Flowers\nYou can also find our products at the Georgetown Farmers\' Market.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:57:17', '2021-04-16 05:57:17', 0, ''),
(72, 5, '81', '', 'Meat, produce, flour, eggs, or sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'Reroot organic is a small, diversified farm producing local, organic and handcrafted food in the fertile soil of Wellington County. Established in 2007 on borrowed land, in 2010 reroot made the exciting move to our very own 70 acre farm in Harriston, Ontario.\n\nReroot products are available through the Community Shared Agriculture (CSA) program, and at the weekly Elora Farmers’ Market.  More details on Reroot Organic’s CSA program here.\n\nThey grow certified organic produce, raise pastured poultry, berkshire pork, produce free-range eggs and keep honeybees.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:56', '2021-04-16 06:04:56', 0, ''),
(73, 5, '80', '', 'Erin/Rockwood, Town of Erin Beef, or sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'A small mixed farm using organic and sustainable practices to grow vegetables and pastured meats.\n\nOffering:\n\nGrass Finished Beef\nPastured Pork\nFree Range Eggs\nPastured Rabbit\nVegetables\nCSA\nCut Flowers\nYou can also find our products at the Georgetown Farmers\' Market.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:32', '2021-04-16 06:02:32', 0, ''),
(74, 5, '82', '', 'Eggs from pasture raised chickens and ducks, whole duck meat and pepperettes, boxes of pork.', 'RiverBound Farms is a small family operation offering heritage breed chicks, ducklings, breeders and layers. Eggs from pasture raised chickens and ducks. Contact to inquire about availability of whole duck meat, pepperettes, pork boxes, and maple syrup.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:02', '2021-04-16 06:02:02', 0, ''),
(75, 5, '83', '', 'Apples, u-pick in season, apple butter, apple cider, honey.', 'We are a family-owned and operated apple orchard. During normal (good harvest) years, we are open to the public during the harvest season, starting Labor Day weekend, on Saturdays from 10:00 am to 4:00 pm and Sundays from 12:00 pm to 4:00 pm.  Once harvest is completed (usually around the end of October), we typically are open Saturdays 10:00 am to 4:00 pm.  Check our website for updates on operating hours, as everything depends on how good the crop is that year.\n\nCall ahead for visits during the week.\n\nMust Taste Item: Cortland Apple\n\nWe offer other farm fresh products available year-round:\n\nApple butter - no artificial colours, flavours or added sugar...healthy and delicious!\nFresh-pressed sweet apple cider - no additives, no preservatives...just pure, pressed apple juice!\nLocal honey - made by our neighbours... get it while quantities last!\nAbout Our Sweet Apple Cider:\n\nOur cider contains NO additives and NO preservatives.\nALL our cider is produced using fresh, hand-picked, tree-ripened fruit -- we use NO grounders, dirty or damaged fruit.\nALL our cider apples are picked into and shipped in bleach-treated bins.\nALL our apple cider is UV-sterilized. UV-sterilization achieves the same food safety effect as pasteurizing but without heat, thereby preserving the unique flavour and nutritional properties of fresh cider that would otherwise be diminished or lost by thermal cooking.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:56:00', '2021-04-16 05:56:00', 0, ''),
(76, 5, '84', '', 'Belwood, Centre Wellington Township Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'Salad Days Farm is a Belwood, Ontario based CSA farm dedicated to feeding people delicious, organic, nutrient-dense food.\n\nOur philosophy is simple: healthy soils grow nutritious vegetables.\n\nAt Salad Days Farm we use organic methods that work with nature rather than against it, to promote diverse and abundant soil life to feed our plants. By caring for the soil we can grow food without the use of chemical fertilizer, pesticides or herbicides. Our goal as farmers is to provide our community with healthy food, while conserving and even improving the health of our soil.\n\nORGANIC VEGETABLES\nWe grow over 30 different types of vegetables including the staples your family loves and unique varieties they don\'t know they love yet.\n\nVegetables:\narugula, beans, beets, bok choy, broccoli, Brussels sprouts, cabbage, carrots, cauliflower, celery, celeriac, collards, cucumbers, eggplants, fennel, garlic, green onions, kale, kohlrabi, leeks, lettuce, mustard greens, Napa cabbage, onions, parsnips, peas, peppers, potatoes, pumpkins, radishes, rapini, salad mix, spinach, sweet corn, Swiss chard, tomatoes, turnips, winter squash, and zucchini.\n\nHerbs:\nbasil, chives, cilantro, dill, mint, parsley, rosemary, sage, and thyme.\n\nIf there are any vegetables missing that you\'d like us to grow, please let us know!\n\nFREE RANGE EGGS\nOur happy hens spend their days scratching and foraging on fresh pasture. As a result, their eggs have a taste and appearance that cannot be found in store-bought eggs. An egg share can be added to your CSA share for a cost of $5 per dozen. We\'ll let you know when eggs become available!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:57:26', '2021-04-16 05:57:26', 0, ''),
(77, 5, '85', '', 'Maple syrup, turkey products', 'Buy local. Buy quality. Our goal is to produce the best quality product for you.\n\nTurkeys and turkey cuts that are naturaly grown with no additives and GMO free fed. Meat is vacuum slealed and fresh frozen.\n\nWe have four kinds of Sausage, Plain, Garlic, Cranberry Maple and Maple Smoked (with Maple syrup) GMO-Free and Gluten-Free.\n\nWe also offer maple syrup, firewood and straw bales for sale.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:04:43', '2021-04-16 06:04:43', 0, ''),
(78, 5, '86', '', 'Alma, Mapleton Township Closed for the season.', 'Springmead farm has organically managed apple orchards that boast nearly 40 varieties of Canadian and heirloom variety apples. These apples suit a wide array of uses including baking, fresh eating, fresh and hard cider. Bees are kept on site to pollinate the orchards and provide an extra sweet treat each autumn.\n\nOur products can also be found at the University of Waterloo\'s Environmental Studies Coffee Shop.\n\nMust Taste Item: Macoun Blend Hot Cider', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:55:08', '2021-04-16 05:55:08', 0, ''),
(79, 5, '87', '', 'Spring annuals, veg and herb plants, veg seeds, seed potatoes and Dutch sets', 'Growing high quality food is not just a job, but our way of life!\n\nAs farmers, we are motivated by a deep love for the land and a desire to share the goodness of homegrown with you and your family.\n\nWhen we started farming in 1992 as newly weds, we were continuing a family tradition of agriculture. Gradually our kitchen and flower gardens expanded. The hobby greenhouse was replaced by larger greenhouses, and the vegetable garden moved out of the yard and into the farm fields.\n\nEvery year we grow and harvest hay, wheat and corn to supply our cattle with feed and bedding. Our greenhouse and farm market feature a wide variety of seasonal plants and produce from Mother’s Day to Thanksgiving.\n\nSome of the crops grown here include strawberries, lettuces, bunching and bulb onions, peas, beans, corn, potatoes, cucumbers, squash, cabbage and much more.\n\nMUST TASTE ITEM: Our exceptional Romaine Lettuce\n\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:26', '2021-04-16 06:07:26', 0, ''),
(80, 5, '88', '', 'Guelph, Guelph Eramosa Township Closed for the season', 'Strom’s Farm and Bakery is a second generation farm started in 1978 with Jay’s love for sweet corn. Jay and Marg started with one acre of sweet corn then added pumpkins in 1996. Channing, their oldest son, returned to the farm in 2000 with his wife Amy. In 2002, they added a corn maze and in 2006 Channing and Amy bought the farm and added a bakery. Channing and Amy, along with their two sons, invite you to visit our farm for quality produce and an exceptional fall experience!\n\nWe pride ourselves in the freshest produce and are known for our exceptional Sweet Corn. Your sweet corn is picked fresh throughout the day (never more than two hours off the stalk) and we only pick the top cob (a stalk has two). We recommend eating your corn the day you pick it up.\n\nWe also love the colour orange! You know October is just around the corner when we fill our front yard with 7,000 pumpkins! Choose from those or pick your own from the patch. Check out our Corn and Pumpkin recipes for your fall harvest gatherings.\n\nSweet Corn, Pumpkins, Baking from scratch, seasonal vegetables/melons, Harvest Fun admission area includes corn and various mazes, pedal karts, pumpkin chuckin and wagon rides. Our Bakery includes Pies, Tarts, Scones, Cookies, Pizza and much more. Our pies are made from scratch daily at our farm in the bakery. Try one today!\n\nMUST TASTE ITEM: Fresh baked Butter Tarts!\n\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:34', '2021-04-16 06:03:34', 0, ''),
(81, 5, '89', '', 'Conn, Wellington North Township Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', '\nTerra Verde Homestead is a 10 acre farm in northern Wellington County. 1.5 acres of the farm is dedicated to a market garden and Community Supported Agriculture (CSA) with the remaining acres in pasture and nut and fruit tree plantings. This diversity is complemented by honeybees and heirloom chickens, and Guinea Fowl. We also have a menagerie of animals including Kune Kune pigs, Nigerian Dwarf dairy goats, alpacas, and a llama.\n\nOffering fresh vegetables, fruits, herbs, free-range eggs, honey, and beeswax candles.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:00:49', '2021-04-16 06:00:49', 0, '');
