(82, 5, '90', '', 'Meats, grocery items, baking and more', 'Thatcher Farms is located on 140 acres in Eramosa Township, in beautiful Wellington County. Our family owned and operated farm offers customers locally produced meat products that are naturally raised and hormone free.\n\nKnowing where your food comes from and how it is grown is an essential ingredient when looking to buy fresh, quality, sustainable meats. At Thatcher Farms you will meet your local farmer and you will learn how buying locally produced meats, eggs, cheeses, honey and syrup help to support and preserve local agriculture. Buying from farmers in your community is not only a healthy choice for your family but demonstrates respect for our land and the environment. Buying your fresh meats from Thatcher Farms means you can buy with confidence!\n\nWe now offer raw pet foods, smoked bones and treats! Our pet foods are a beautiful mixture of beef, pork, and lamb organ meats. You can purchase our raw pet foods, raw beef, lamb or pork bones, smoked bones and our famous smoked Pig\'s Ears at our Country Store as well as the Guelph Farmers\' Market!\n\nThatcher Farms also offers beautifully created Gift Baskets tailored exactly for you. Baskets can include bread, butter tarts, squares, any meat cut (ie: sausages, chops, steaks, roasts), honey, maple syrup, milk, eggs, cheese, coffee, jam, meat pies, nachos, salsa and more.\n\nMUST TASTE ITEM: Bacon Jam', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:25', '2021-04-16 06:05:25', 0, ''),
(83, 5, '91', '', 'Located just minutes from the Aberfoyle Farmers\' Market.', 'During app season, each week we offer a wide variety of apples including Gala, Courtland, Honey Crisp and more. We also press our fresh cider.\n\nFarm Market OPEN every Friday and Saturday from 12:00 am - 6:00 p.\n\nSpecialty coffee freshly roasted on site, butter tarts, apple turnovers (both freshly baked and frozen) and sour dough bread. Produce when in season.\n\n ', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-08-03', '2021-08-03', 1, '2021-08-03 12:06:39', '2021-08-03 12:06:39', 0, ''),
(84, 5, '92', '', 'Meats, eggs, grocery items', 'Top quality meats from 5th generation family farmers.\n\nOffering grass grazed and pasture raised lamb, goat, heritage pork, duck, goose, chicken, turkey and rabbit. Gluten-free products available (sausage and more).\n\nCall before visiting. Year round.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:20', '2021-04-16 06:05:20', 0, ''),
(85, 5, '93', '', 'Rockwood, Guelph Eramosa Township Not open yet for the season', 'Committed to providing the freshest produce at an affordable price. We are a self serve facility that is open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, from mid May to the end of October.\n\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:57', '2021-04-16 06:06:57', 0, ''),
(86, 5, '94', '', 'Puslinch, City of Hamilton Honey', 'Tuckamore Bee Company is a supplier of honey and honey related products.\n\nHoney: Available in raw, liquid and churned. It comes in 500g and 1 kg jars.\n\nBeeswax Products: Lip Balm, Foodsafe Wood Polish, Leather Protector and Ultra Rich Skin Food.\n\nQueens, Cells and Nucleus Colonies: We specialize in selling bees to beekeepers. Alison transitioned from a researcher with the Ontario Beekeepers’ Association to a queen producer, bringing with her the skills to select honey bee stock for disease resistant characteristics.\n\nWhere to Buy:\n\nIgnatius Farm and CSA, Guelph/Eramosa\nGuelph Farmers\' Market, City of Guelph\nPlanet Bean, 3 locations in the City of Guelph', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:37', '2021-04-16 06:06:37', 0, ''),
(87, 5, '95', '', 'Organic fresh and processed food', 'Tully\'s Way Farm is a private farm of 78 acres located just a few kilometres south-east of Guelph about 60 kilometres west of Toronto just north of the 401. We specialize in heritage types of vegetables and fruit, heritage chicken, eggs. Our organic products are available year-round\n\nMust Taste Item: Honey, Organic Chicken', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:50', '2021-04-16 06:05:50', 0, ''),
(88, 5, '96', '', 'Selling leafy greens and herbs', 'Uprooted Farm is a controlled environment agriculture (CEA), hydroponic container farm in Elora, Ontario. It is a self-contained growing machine! Production in a controlled environment mitigates weather, pest and weed issues associated with outdoor growing, while allowing control over light, temperature, humidity and nutrients. We produce greens, lettuces and herbs year-round without the use of pesticides. Each week, we deliver over 1000 plants to local retailers, restaurants, farmers\' markets and families. Uprooted Farm is the first farming unit of it\'s kind in southern Ontario. We use plant-based, compostable packaging. #freshlocal365  \n\nFarmer Donna is herself Uprooted, and (ironically uncontained) being a transplant from Newfoundland! Her interest in gardening and growing food started as a child in North Harbour Placentia Bay, NL helping her grandmother pick rocks and grow vegetables, but her passion for it was realized when she and her husband Gary purchased their property in Elora in 2005. On their 3/4 acre property, Donna has successfully farmed root crops, greens, herbs and fruit.  #uncontainedfarmer\n\nMust Taste: Everything!\n\nOur produce is available to restaurants and wholesale, or at the following locations:\n\nFraberts Fresh Food, Fergus\nDar\'s Country Market, Elora\nSante, Elora\nElora Farmer\'s Market', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:02', '2021-04-16 06:07:02', 0, ''),
(89, 5, '97', '', 'Fergus, Centre Wellington Township Closed for the season', 'Our specialty is our great tasting corn, which is picked fresh for you every morning. We sell it at our farm, as well as at our corn stands. You can also find our sweet corn at Fraberts Fresh Food in downtown Fergus, or the New to You Farmers&rsquo; Market on Highway 6 N in Fergus. Discounts are given for 10+ dozen.\n\nWe are a family-run farm also selling our own fresh garden produce, maple syrup, and eggs.\n\nWe also sell our own mini sunflowers, asparagus (May/June), garden vegetables in season, and fresh pick or dried romano beans. In the summer months we raise turkeys and meat chickens, which will be available near Thanksgiving.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:02:38', '2021-04-16 06:02:38', 0, ''),
(90, 5, '98', '', 'Organic vegetables (uncertified)', 'We are a 1 acre mixed vegetable market garden and greenhouse offering mixed vegetables, greens, herbs, and flowers. We grow following the principles of Agroecology, and to meet or do better than the Canadian organic standards though we are currently uncertified.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:05:55', '2021-04-16 06:05:55', 0, ''),
