(92, 5, '100', '', 'Whole pastured chickens, vegetables, eggs. Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', 'Winterhill Farm and Garden is a small family farm located on 106 acres in the Township of Eramosa in beautiful Wellington County providing customers with organic vegetable farm shares (CSA\'s) and fresh pastured eggs from happy hens.\n\nMust Taste Items: Fresh Local Organic Vegetables and Pastured Eggs.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:01:55', '2021-04-16 06:01:55', 0, ''),
(93, 5, '101', '', 'Pre-cut, cut your own, fresh greenery, pots and more', '\nWe are a family-owned and run Christmas tree farm that caters to families by providing a healthy and happy Christmas experience. The memory of family outings in the fresh air, enjoying a hayride together to choose the perfect Christmas tree, will last a lifetime.\n\nLocated about an hour west of Toronto, we provide a full-service experience in selecting your Christmas tree, wreaths, garland and other decorative greenery. We have 75 acres of Christmas trees at various stages of growth that provides a great selection for your family to choose from.\n\nTake a lovely ride through the country, and upon arrival at the farm, our hosts will be happy to guide you through the process and answer any questions you may have. Hop on the hayride or take a walk out to the field where you can take your time picking the perfect tree. Once you have your tree, we will shake it and bale it. All services are included in the cost of your tree. Afterwards, warm up in our snack bar with hot chocolate or hot apple cider, hot dog or apple pie at family-friendly prices.\n\nCome to the farm, start Christmas off with a nice tradition.\n\nWe are open 7 days a week from November 16 until December 22, 2019, 9:00am to 5:00pm\n\nBlue Spruce\nMyer Spruce\nWhite Spruce\nNorway Spruce\nBalsam Fir\nFraser Fir\nMust Have Item: Handmade Garlands', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:15', '2021-04-16 06:06:15', 0, ''),
(94, 5, '102', '', 'Cremini, Portabello and Bellini mushrooms', 'At W&T Mushrooms, our focus is on growing Cremini and Portabello mushrooms on a commercial scale supplying the local and competitive Southern Ontario market. We love what we do, while #playinginshit and creating a quality product is our passion!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:01:03', '2021-04-16 06:01:03', 0, ''),
(95, 5, '103', '', 'Hillsburgh, Town of Erin Sign up for farm share (CSA programme)', '\n‘Zocalo’ steams from the Aztec meaning of a community hub; relying on friends, family and neighbors to support the harvest. Sebastian and Bethany manage the 83-acre property between Guelph and Hillsburgh that boasts greenhouses, gardens, hayfields, cedar forests, conservation wetland and a small orchard. The farm uses ecological farming methods to provide customers with nutrient dense, fresh, organic produce without synthetic chemicals, artificial fertilizers or GMOs.\n\nZocalo sells their produce, including carrots, garlic, spinach, tomatoes, broccoli and signature salad greens to households through their Community Shared Agriculture Program (CSA).\n\nAlthough they are a smaller farm, the Zocalo team is committed to growing delicious Organic produce while influencing climate change, soil erosion and water conservation for years to come.\n\nMust Taste Item: Signature Salad Greens', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:03:56', '2021-04-16 06:03:56', 0, ''),
(96, 5, '115', '', 'Near legendary Mennonite bacon all day breakfast…', 'Just like a classic roadside diner, we pride ourselves on our down home atmosphere and quality of our food. Come on in, browse our daily specials and daily soup, and enjoy a bottomless cup of coffee along with your meal. We are well also near legendary for the Mennonite bacon we serve with our all day breakfast.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"  ', 1, '2021-03-31', '2021-03-31', 1, '2021-03-31 12:50:11', '2021-03-31 12:50:11', 0, ''),
(97, 5, '116', '', 'tasty eats | choice coffee | unique gifts | great games', 'Around 1993, Heidi, designer, baker and soul of Rumbletum Café & Gifts, honed her unstoppable entrepreneurial spirit. She began with folk art painting on little boxes and other household items as gifts to our family and friends. This lead to small craft shows around the Kitchener/Waterloo area. As often happens with art, Heidi’s style evolved and became more focused on a line of hand painted children’s clothing. This lead to larger, further away craft & gift shows, and early morning market booths.\n\nOur location is the perfect place for us...and you!  It has a cozy, welcoming vibe, and we have made so many friends that have enriched our lives so much, it makes coming to work something we look forward to.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:37', '2021-04-16 06:07:37', 0, ''),
(98, 5, '117', '', 'Delicious Pastries, Gourmet Paninis, and More!', 'Founded in 1994, Capistrano became one of Downtown Guelph’s original coffee houses. Then known as Capistrano Caffe Bar, or simply Capistrano’s, it’s original vision was to give those who worked, lived or visited Downtown Guelph a great experience of fresh brewed coffee and quick-serve food choices with an Italian style.\n\nToday Capistrano Bistro & Espresso Bar continues to take pride in providing the highest quality beverages and food service with a European flair. Our carefully selected espresso, coffees & teas, freshly baked pastries and house-made menu items all demonstrate our commitment to providing each of our customers something we all want – simply the best.\n\nLocated in St. Georges Square in the heart of Downtown, come in for a visit, enjoy the experience and when someone asks \"so where do you want to meet?\" simply say... \"I’ll see you at Capistrano’s!\"', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-01', '2021-04-01', 1, '2021-04-01 13:43:14', '2021-04-01 13:43:14', 0, ''),
(99, 5, '118', '', 'Providing front-line poverty relief and social assistance in Guelph', 'Our Mission\n\nProviding tangible, compassionate assistance and care to those in the Guelph community and abroad through immediate relief and ongoing support with the goal of a greater level of independence.\n\nOur Core Values\n\nDignity – We acknowledge the inherent dignity and worth of every human being.\nCompassion – We treat everyone in a compassionate, dignified manner, no matter their current challenges and needs.\nEncouragement – We encourage individuals and families to grow in a safe and caring environment by recognizing their inherent dignity and worth.\n\nWhat we do\n- Immediate Relief\n- Ongoing Support\n- Community Projects', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:06:26', '2021-04-16 06:06:26', 0, ''),
(100, 5, '119', '', 'Proudly serving customers & our community since 1993.', 'Continuing a legacy left by former store owner, Vahid Walji, New Age Health Food + Supplements in Guelph is committed to listening to customers to better understand their needs and advise them on the best choices for their health and a healthy lifestyle.  \n\nAlso, we have very large selection of beeswax candles.  Tapers, votives, and fancy, too!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-10-21', '2021-10-21', 1, '2021-10-21 11:20:03', '2021-10-21 11:20:03', 1, 'Beautiful beeswax candles for you!  Enjoy our large selection of beeswax candles.  Tapers, votives, and fancy, too!'),
(101, 5, '120', '', 'Acupuncture, Reflexology, and More', 'Easternwell Clinic provides holistic health care for the Guelph community, healing the body, spirit, and mind. \n\nWe offer various traditional Chinese healing modalities, such as acupuncture, gua sha, cupping, meridian massage, foot reflexology, herbal remedies, ear seeds, and cosmetic acupuncture. \n\nAdditionally, we also have an over-the-counter pharmacy with many traditional and popular herbal formulas to help you with a holistic recovery.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:54:30', '2021-04-16 05:54:30', 0, ''),
(102, 5, '121', '', 'Welcome to Guelph City Hall', 'Should you require anything while visiting our fine City, do not hesitate to drop by our visitor information centre, located inside city hall.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:07:59', '2021-04-16 06:07:59', 0, ''),
(103, 5, '122', '', 'Celebrating Guelph’s stories!', 'The Guelph Civic Museum showcases Guelph’s history through permanent and changing exhibits, a fun and interactive families gallery, and special events and activities. \n\nLocated in the renovated Loretto Convent, the Guelph Civic Museum is home to a collection of over 30,000 artifacts that bring Guelph’s past to life.\n\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:59:11', '2021-04-16 05:59:11', 0, ''),
(104, 5, '123', '', '80-acre park located in the north end of Guelph', 'Riverside park is an 80-acre park located in the north end of Guelph and is built around a portion of the Speed River.\n\nThe park opened in 1905, spanning 14.5 acres. Its development was related to Guelph\'s now discontinued streetcar system. The park was a stop on one of the Guelph Radial Railway\'s streetcar line, and the company held a contest in 1905 to name the new attraction. The name \"Riverside Park\", based on the site\'s proximity to the Speed River, was the winning selection. Since its foundation the park has expanded to 80-acres, with many on-site features and has become a noted landmark and attraction in the city. Riverside also hosts a number of events each year, many of which have become longstanding traditions in the city.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:53:13', '2021-04-16 05:53:13', 0, ''),
(105, 5, '124', '', 'Birthplace of \"In Flanders Fields\" author John McCrae', 'McCrae House, located in Guelph, Ontario, is the birthplace of John McCrae (b. 1872 – d. 1918), doctor, soldier and author of the famous First World War poem \"In Flanders Fields\". The house is a National Historic Site of Canada.\n\nThis small limestone cottage, built in 1858, was owned by the McCrae family from 1870 to 1873. Other families occupied the house until 1966, when a group of Guelph citizens purchased the building with the intention of preserving it as a museum. This group formed the Lt. Col. John McCrae Birthplace Society and began to raise money for its restoration.\n\nMcCrae House contains both permanent and temporary exhibition space that interprets the life and times of John McCrae. Yearly themes are offered. Summer activities include Poppy Push, Canada Day, Teddy Bear Picnic, History Camp and special teas in the garden. The gardening volunteers have worked to create an award-winning garden reflecting the time period of the mid-to-late 19th century.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:57:36', '2021-04-16 05:57:36', 0, ''),
(106, 5, '125', '', 'Your downtown fine dining destination.', 'Proprietors:\n\nExecutive Chef – Graham Black\\nRestauranteur – Gus Cripouris\n\nLocated in the heart of downtown Guelph, Bin 23 offers a North American continental menu with multicultural flair along with daily features. Enjoy unrivaled consignment wines from around the world along with an extensive wine cellar. Relax in award winning ambiance and enjoy diverse music selections while being pampered by a team of professionals.\n\nBin 23 offers a unique dining experience with a seasonal menu options from locally sourced farms, bakery’s, grocers & distributors as well as daily features and desserts all made in-house!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 14:26:34', '2021-06-25 14:26:34', 0, ''),
(107, 5, '126', '', 'A romantic setup inspired by European dessert cafés.', 'We specialize in crepes, coffee, lattes, ice cream waffle cones and many other amazing treats.\n\nHow to build your own mouth-watering delicious crepe:\n1.  Select Your Base:  Are you in the mood for a crepe or waffle?\n2.  Select Your Ice Cream:  Choose from any one of our 8 premium ice cream flavours.\n3.  Select Your Toppings:  Fresh fruit to decadent sweets, we have over 30 topping choices. Savoury options too!\n4.  Select Your Sauce:  Salty caramel truffle, Belgian milk chocolate, Nutella and many more.\n\nNOTE re: HOURS:  Saturday and Sunday we are CLOSED from 3pm-6pm.  See you before or after!\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 05:53:47', '2021-04-16 05:53:47', 0, ''),
(108, 5, '127', '', 'Driverseat is your one-stop shop for transportation solutions.', 'Night on the town?  Let us get you - and your car - home safe and sound.  Give us a call and we will take care of the rest.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-16', '2021-04-16', 1, '2021-04-16 06:01:38', '2021-04-16 06:01:38', 0, ''),
(109, 5, '128', '', 'Visit our locally owned ice cream and coffee shop!', 'Visit our locally owned ice cream and coffee shop. We primarily use local ingredients and serve freshly made waffle cones, desserts and delicious coffee. We also make scrumptious ice cream cakes for all occasions. Come in and enjoy our comfortable atmosphere, quality treats, and warm service.', 'Be sure to tell them Dux sent you!  ', 1, '2021-04-13', '2021-04-13', 1, '2021-04-13 11:38:04', '2021-04-13 11:38:04', 0, ''),
(110, 5, '129', '', 'Excellence in dining, with country cozy charm', 'Aberfoyle Mill is just outside the city of Guelph, in the quiet hamlet of Aberfoyle, just outside the city of Guelph.  We invite you to enjoy our rich heritage, superb food, and charming service.\n\nThe delightful interior of the Aberfoyle Mill is a constant reminder of its history.\n\nThe Mill was built in 1859 by a Scottish immigrant named George McLean. The village of Aberfoyle was named after a small village below the Trossachs mountains, about 40 km north of Glasgow, by another Scottsman named George MacFarlane. The Mill Originally functioned as a grist mill, powered by the pond situated at the back of the building. In 1867, the Mill won a gold medal, for its oatmeal at the World’s Fair in Paris. The Mill functioned until the late 1920’s.\n\nIn 1960 the Mill was purchased by the Owens family and after about 6 years of restoration, it was converted into one of the most unique restaurants in Canada.\n\nThrough a vestibule you enter the main dining area where the decor is made up of authentic antiques, one of the countries largest personal collections of Canadiana.', 'Be sure to tell them Dux sent you!  ', 1, '2021-04-13', '2021-04-13', 1, '2021-04-13 12:25:03', '2021-04-13 12:25:03', 0, ''),
