(157, 5, '114', '', 'Exploring food, places, and people.', 'Award-winning, locally flavoured food & drink tasting tours. We are telling the stories of the people and the places that give Wellington County its flavour, through the cuisine that gives this slice of Southwestern Ontario its magic. Join us off the beaten path, come take a Detour.\n\nWe want to share our love of Wellington County by pointing out the culinary links between our rural heritage and our growers and makers of today. This region has deep agricultural roots, so food – fresh, good, local, food – comes naturally to us. We celebrate the power of a full plate, cup, or bowl, to bring people and communities together.\n\nAll of our experiences harness the power of storytelling. At Taste Detours, we aim to celebrate our regional heritage by uncovering the stories found within small towns and mid-sized cities via local flavour — offering the opportunity to learn some little-known lore of the area, and to hear directly from local food and drink purveyors themselves. Unique locales where you have to dig a bit deeper to unearth a true “taste of place”.\nConnect and contribute to a thriving Wellington County\n\nMostly we want to facilitate connections. Connections made between these innovative restaurateurs, chefs, farmers, brewers, cheesemakers, bakers, and their use of the surrounding agriculture. Connections between each other too, by simply slowing down and breaking bread together. Something humans do all over the world.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-04-15', '2021-04-15', 1, '2021-04-15 15:26:00', '2021-04-15 15:26:00', 0, ''),
(158, 5, '176', '', 'Glenda Knows Guelph!', 'Professional real estate agent at RE/MAX Real Estate Centre with +20 years of experience. Committed to excellence (and to you!).\n\nIt\'s truly my pleasure to have helped so many new families find their first home, empty nesters downsize to something that perfectly fits their needs, and growing families upsize to the home of their dreams - with plenty of space so no one steps on each other\'s toes!  I\'ve worked consistently with the same Clients over many years, buying and selling for them as their needs change.  Many I consider to be part of my close family.\n\nHaving lived in Guelph seemingly forever, I have an intimate knowledge of neighbourhoods both old and new.  And I always provide pointers and insider tips on how to really find your perfect home and avoid the ones that present well but are full of the kind of headaches you simply don\'t need.\n\nGet in touch and we\'ll get you settled into your next place.  ', 'Be sure to mention that \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 11:02:14', '2021-06-25 11:02:14', 0, ''),
