(514, 5, '527', '', 'Classic sweet tooth fixes here!', 'From old-school classics to the latest candy crazes, you\'ll find them all at Sweet!  We\'ve got the hard-to-finds, the Euro and Asian imports, fresh Turkish delight and fudge, and delicately delightful treats for those special someones in your life.  Your sweet tooth will thank you.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 14:22:55', '2021-06-25 14:22:55', 0, ''),
(515, 5, '528', '', 'Best local craft beer pub since 2011.', 'Since we started Baker Street Station, all of us have known exactly what kind of pub we wanted our place to be. It needed to reflect the time-tested tradition of great English public houses while at the same time bringing a fresh new perspective to the classic pub experience.\n\nOur menu is fresh yet traditional. Our atmosphere is classic yet infused with a modern flair. Our beverage selections reflect what we believe the best both Ontario and the world have to offer.\n\nWe want every dining experience to reflect our dedication to the rich tradition of public houses past while at the same time giving our guests something new, fresh and inspired.\n\nWelcome to our Pub!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 14:47:18', '2021-06-25 14:47:18', 0, ''),
(516, 5, '529', '', 'A casual restaurant and bar located in downtown Guelph.', 'Bobby O\'Brien\'s is a casual restaurant and bar located in downtown Guelph with unbelievable daily food and drink specials, live music, and a friendly-casual atmosphere; it\'s impossible to beat! Bobby O\'Brien\'s is Guelph\'s oldest and warmest and has become a staple Irish pub among the locals welcoming regulars and new customers alike. We are downtown Guelph\'s Sports bar! We offer a great traditional pub atmosphere, with 19 beers on tap and a casual dining menu at reasonable prices. With 8 large screen TVs, and a 12 foot big screen and cozy seating, Bobby O\'Brien\'s is the perfect place to meet with friends and unwind, eat and catch the latest PPV event.\n\nClose proximity to the Sleeman Centre and River Run Centre makes us a great meeting place before or after the game or show. We also do parties and catering.\n\nWelcome to our Pub!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 14:53:24', '2021-06-25 14:53:24', 0, ''),
(517, 5, '530', '', 'Good ingredients matter.', 'Earth to Table: Bread Bar is a living extension of the food philosophy that began when writing the Earth to Table cookbook.  Earth to Table celebrates what is best about food and is trying to shorten the gap between producers and consumer.  \n\nBread Bar celebrates and cooks with the seasons.  We offer handcrafted food, made with the finest ingredients for people who want a better quality meal. \n\nGood Ingredients Matter.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 14:58:40', '2021-06-25 14:58:40', 0, ''),
(518, 5, '531', '', 'Great food.  Great wine.', 'At Buon Gusto, we have a passion for keeping things simple.  We use high-quality, often locally sourced ingredients.  Our full bar features local craft beers, an extensive and reasonably priced old world wine selection, as well as top-shelf spirits and classic cocktails.\n\nOur woodburning oven, made in Reggello, Tuscany, is ‘il cuore’ (the heart) of Buon Gusto.  We import tipo 00 flour and San Marzano tomatoes from Italy, to make our pizzas in the traditional Neapolitan thin-crust style, hearth-baking them at 900 degrees Fahrenheit for just 90 seconds.  Our menu also features salads, pastas and small-plate antipasti, made by following family recipes as well as traditional regional dishes.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 15:02:08', '2021-06-25 15:02:08', 0, ''),
(519, 5, '532', '', 'Japanese inspired. Locally influenced. House made.', 'We make our noodles in house daily using only Canadian wheat. All our broths are made with pure water that has been filtered through our reverse osmosis water purification system, which not only makes a cleaner, more full-flavoured stock, but also gets the most nutrients out of the ingredients. \n\nThe meat-based broths are made with locally sourced meat and bones supplied to us by Trotters Butcher Shop. We use whole chickens in our chicken stock, and a combination of smoked pork hocks and duck bones in our rich stock. Our vegetarian broth is made from a combination of cherry tomatoes, kombu seaweed and shiitake mushrooms.\n\nAt Crafty Ramen we are always trying to improve the flavour of our product by refining our techniques and using higher-quality, more local ingredients, when available – all to provide a better product, and ultimately a better experience for you.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-25', '2021-06-25', 1, '2021-06-25 15:07:09', '2021-06-25 15:07:09', 0, ''),
