(536, 5, '552', '', 'Your flower shop destination.', 'Located on quaint Wilson Street in historic downtown you will find Guelph florist, Sweet Violets.  Lush seasonal outdoor displays welcome you inside.  Once in the door you are embraced with a sense of Old World Europe. An all-white interior provides a crisp backdrop to the burst of colour and foliage.  Down a few steps you enter the bustling creative workshop…the heart of the business.\n\nMs. Kelli O started the Sweet Violets journey 12 years ago. Shortly followed by Sara …..a few short years later came Brenna aka “bear” and then our newbie Krystal.  At the corner of Wilson and Macdonnell you will find compassion, comfort, ambition, humour, loyalty, love sometimes frustration and yes more humour.  We each bring something special to this quirky little shop. The puzzle pieces fit and we are truly fortunate to have found our way here. \n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-29', '2021-06-29', 1, '2021-06-29 14:31:55', '2021-06-29 14:31:55', 0, ''),
(537, 5, '551', '', 'We tempt any and many.', 'A beautiful view and location to compliment this bakery café on Carden Street.  We have fresh croissants, breads, pastries that could tempt any and many.\n\nWhat\'s in a name?\n\nThe name of the shop has a story, part of which started in Guelph! In the midst of putting together this bakery, among applications for construction and business, Eric was at City Hall putting together some paperwork. The phone in the office rang, where the person on the other end was told, \"I\'m just with Eric the Baker here, I\'ll have to call you back.\" And the name has stuck since!\n\nThe Story Behind it All:\n\nWe work to achieve the familiar flavours of Eric heritage, which lie in the teachings of his family. Such a love for food and flavour would be wrong not to share, let alone taste!\n\nIt all started with his grandmother, who opened one of the first bakeries in Toronto, on Yonge Street (Le Petit Gourmet). This is where Eric spent a great deal of his Canadian upbringing, by staying out of childhood mischief and learning how to bake with his dear grandmother! She was the first to teach him how to roll a croissant and to set him on his path in creating delicious and wholesome baked goods.\n\nHis grandmother\'s two sons, Eric\'s uncles, set the precedent for Eric\'s future, by opening restaurants and bakeries in Toronto, Australia, and Elora, and continuing the philosophy of real food done right, through tradition. Their restaurants and stores (Maison Basque, Cafe du Marche) reflected their upbringing in the Basque country, and the familiar flavours that reminded them of home.\n\nNow Eric has continued to carry the family torch with opening several places alongside his uncle Roger, including Cinnamon, a prior bakeshop in Elora, as well as La Cuisine, in Australia.\n\nIn an effort to move closer to his dear uncle Roger, he was graced by a marvellous location across from City Hall on Carden Street, his current home, where he\'s chosen to share his beloved tradition with Guelph. Why Guelph? So seldom is there a place like this where tradition and history is so well maintained, reflected, and honoured as they do here!\n\nFood for Thought:\n\nOur menu is fairly traditional, with typical things and inspirations of what one might find in a cafe in France. As we continue to bake furiously, we\'ll try to find out what Guelph really loves, and combine it with what we know and love. Our menu will grow (more cakes to come!), and with your assistance in feedback (please, don\'t be shy!), we can offer something for everyone.\n\nWe\'re open to comments and suggestions, as well as orders and catering.\n\nOur only request that orders are placed either on the phone or in person, NOT on Facebook or Twitter.\n\nWe\'ve gotten some requests for specialty items such as rye, multigrain, and whole wheat breads, as well as gluten free items. We honour these requests, we just ask that you are patient as we work on those recipes, until we are happy with the tasty results.\n\nAllergy/Intolerance/Sensitivity Issues:\n\nWe are an establishment using dairy products, pork products, gluten flours, almonds and walnuts. Anyone with severe allergies or intolerances to those items listed are not recommended to purchase anything without discussing it with an employee first. Thanks for your understanding!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-29', '2021-06-29', 1, '2021-06-29 14:37:14', '2021-06-29 14:37:14', 0, ''),
(538, 5, '547', '', 'Bookstore \'n Cinema \'n Restaurant \'n Bar!', 'We are an independent Bookstore, Cinema, Restaurant, and Bar in Guelph, Ontario.\n\nA bookstore that shows movies.  A cinema that serves dinner.  A bar that launches books.\n\nEnjoy all the unique offerings we have for you!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-29', '2021-06-29', 1, '2021-06-29 14:40:47', '2021-06-29 14:40:47', 0, ''),
(539, 5, '546', '', 'Grab & Go Grilled Wrap Paninis', 'Grab & Go Grilled Wrap Paninis with dine in & delivery.  High quality homemade food from local ladies you can trust.  Homemade fillings.   Killer Sauces.\n\nWelcome, Dee and Jules here, thanks for checking us out! Let’s give you some background info, we’ve been in the Hospitality Industry for over 15 years, with jobs ranging from serving, cooking, baking, managing restaurants and our own food stands. We have had the pleasure of working side by side in a restaurant for the past 5 years. During this time, we’ve shared our values, morals, aspirations, and many tasty dishes! We bring the same style of cooking to the table; homemade, fresh cuisine inspired by our childhoods and travels.\n\nOur dream is to open up a small counter service restaurant in Guelph, but waiting on our dream location has made us impatient. We came to the realization that catering is the best way for us to offer you our tasty Grilled Wrap Paninis. We specialize in business lunches, corporate meetings and training workshops. We’re two hard working ladies committed to serving you delicious scratch made food, using aromatic herbs, lots of love, and lemon zest! When you eat our food, you taste the difference, and you know who’s cooking it. The ingredients are fresh. No processed meats. No condiments that have been sitting on a shelf. Quality you can taste. From people you can trust.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-06-29', '2021-06-29', 1, '2021-06-29 14:42:17', '2021-06-29 14:42:17', 0, ''),
