(558, 5, '110', '', 'Let me bring you amazing culinary experiences.', 'Bringing food to the heart of your most memorable experiences is the passion of Chef Scott Yates. Every element of Chef Scotty\'s creation for you is designed with an eye to your needs, designed to achieve that elegant, gourmet experience or, perhaps, to deliver comfort food options with a twist. He cooks with a deep desire for connections to local farmers, producers, and ingredients. He delivers to meet the vision of bringing families, friends and communities together through food...what love tastes like.\n\nYour Red Seal chef, Scott Yates, has been bringing joy to his customers for almost a decade, whether it\'s touring and dining our Niagara wine region on a Bistro Tour, being a private chef for an intimate gathering, or molding the perfect food around a family event.\n\nScott has extensive catering experience with top establishments in our region and throughout southern Ontario.\n\nHe has created for those magical small gatherings and led teams to serve up to 5,000 guests, including three of Canada’s Prime Ministers and innumerable celebrities.\n\nChef Scotty has created experiences alongside celebrity chefs Michael Smith, Anna Olson, Lynn Crawford, Mark McEwen, Giada De Laurentiis, Bal Arneson and Vikram Vij, to name a few. \n\nChef Scott\'s mission is to bring you lifelong memories through the power of connections over food.', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-08-03', '2021-08-03', 1, '2021-08-03 12:13:04', '2021-08-03 12:13:04', 0, ''),
(559, 5, '572', '', 'Chabad educates and empowers students to live the Joy of Judaism', 'The Chabad house doors at The University of Guelph will always be open to all. It is a place where students can socialize in a comfortable, home-like setting, with friends, food and discussion.\n\nChabad strives to create a warm and welcoming Jewish Student Center, where students can explore their Jewish heritage in a nonjudgmental and friendly atmosphere. Chabad strives to create a center for prayer and study, where one can gain a deeper understanding and appreciation of one’s Jewish heritage. And Chabad strives to create a community for all Jewish students, with opportunities to expand their experiences in all aspects of their college career.\n \nFounded on strong personal relationships, Chabad educates and empowers students to live the Joy of Judaism.  We do this with many social activities where students will gain a deeper understanding and appreciation of their heritage, in a fun, interactive way. We provide for the spiritual and material needs of every Jewish student - regardless of background or affiliation with unconditional love and concern.\n\nWe look forward to personally welcoming you at the Chabad House where you will find warmth, wisdom, and a good time at a House you can call your own!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-08-05', '2021-08-05', 1, '2021-08-05 15:14:22', '2021-08-05 15:14:22', 0, ''),
(560, 5, '573', '', 'Delicious plant-based ice creamy goodness', 'Delicious ice cream should be accessible to everyone!\n\nNo Udder opened in June 2018 as downtown Cambridge’s plant-based ice cream shop. We offer the best in vegan, non-dairy ice cream and frozen desserts – like our popular vegan ice cream cakes – all made in-house! With your dietary needs in mind, we carry many allergy-friendly, gluten-free, and keto-diet alternatives.\n\nWhether you’re a vegan or not, a fan of the waffle cone or loyal to the cup, ordering for one or planning a party, we’ve got the plant-based goodness for you.\n\nVisit us!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-08-05', '2021-08-05', 1, '2021-08-05 15:28:32', '2021-08-05 15:28:32', 0, ''),
