(609, 31, '1008', '', 'Redefining The Dance, Boxing & Fitness Experience In South Etobicoke.', 'Fearless Studios(FS) is redefining what people think about the Dance, Boxing and Fitness industry! FS has created a totally inclusive environment that challenges stereotypes and provides a path for every single member to reach their potential.\n\nFS was co-founded by Professional Boxing Champion Mohammed Abedeen & Professional Dancer Krystal Glazier-Roscoe. Over 30 combined years experience in dance, boxing and fitness locally and all around the world has shown us that Its become entirely to common in these industries to feel as though you are not good enough or will never be good enough! We are breaking down those pressures and by using new technologies, world class training and the right inspiration we are building improved programs that cater to everyone. Through Dance, Boxing and Fitness training we build essential life skills that will inspire and create confident fearless individuals!\n\n\nKrystal Glazier-Roscoe\n\nKrystal began her journey as a baton twirler at a very young age. She competed for over 10 years around Canada and became the 3 time National champion. She worked her way from National Champion to eventually twirling fire! As she grew and sought new challenges she found her passion for dance. She started training and learning from some of the best teachers in Toronto. Performing around the GTA Krystal was apart of many dance company’s and performed in many shows. She graduated from Father John Redmond in the regional arts dance program where she went back for many years as a guest choreographer for their end of year shows. She graduated from George Brown collage in the Commercial dance program where she excelled and developed further as a dancer/choreographer.\n\nKrystal worked with the City of Toronto running dance programs for youth for over 10 years. Krystal gave her heart and soul into each dancer she had the privilege to teach and knew she wanted to do more. This ambition to do more led her to create the Fearless Dance Company. Accepting of all levels, ages, and styles of dance; Krystal made sure that Fearless Dance Company was about building confident individuals and making sure that her students all felt like stars in their own way.\n\nKrystal has taught and choreographed thousands of adult classes at some of Toronto’s most popular studios! Krystal prides herself on translating her professional dance training into fun, creative and challenging classes.\n\nKrystal has been so inspired by all her students throughout her years and will continue to live out her dreams through Fearless Studios. \n\n\nMohammed Abedeen\n\nMohammed realized his passion for boxing when he discovered Muhammad Ali. Muhammad Ali inspired Mohammad to become the best boxer he could be but more importantly he inspired him to be the type of person that changes the lives of others! Mohammed was born and raised in Brampton and Mississauga by a single mom with 4 kids. He saw his mom work relentlessly to ensure his family never needed anything and this left a lifelong impact with him. \n\nAs an amateur boxer Mohammed amassed a career of over 100 fights all over Canada and won many titles at home and abroad. As a professional boxer he went undefeated rising the world professional boxing rankings until he captured the Professional Boxing Championship IBA lightweight Title.\n\nAlong the way he has trained with some of the best in the world alongside Manny Pacquiao, Freddie Roach, Amir Khan, Floyd Mayweather and many other Professional World Champions. “All this experience has been a dream of a lifetime but it comes back to what inspired me to start in the first place. Now that I’ve become a Boxing Champion and gained experience all over the world, the goal is to inspire and hopefully change the lives of others around me just as Muhammad Ali did!”\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"\n\nNOTE:  As this is a \"FreeToBe\" listing, please check in with us prior to visiting, to avoid any disappointments.  Phone is good.  In-person is better.', 1, '2022-01-25', '2022-01-25', 1, '2022-01-25 18:47:42', '2022-01-25 18:47:42', 0, ''),
(610, 31, '1009', '', 'Organic Hair Removal Studio', 'A sweeter more natural way to remove unwanted body hair.\n\nWhat is Body Sugaring?\n\nBody Sugaring is an ancient art of hair removal that uses a completely natural paste made from lemon, sugar and water. Unlike waxes, it does not contain petrochemicals, resins, or preservatives.\n\nThe paste is molded onto your skin against the direction of the hair growth, then quickly flicked off, removing the sugar paste. This process extracts your unwanted hair and collects dead skin cells while exfoliating your skin.\n\nThis ancient hand technique, allows the hair to be extracted in the direction of its growth which leads to less breakage and discomfort for you! BodySugar is more sanitary and reduces waste because there are no sticks or strips used. After your service, the paste and gloves are discarded and you are left with beautifully smooth skin.\nHow Long Does Body Sugaring Last?\n\nFor the best results, book your appointments when the hair is 1/8? long. At 1/8? the hair is in the beginning stage of growth and after extraction it will take longer to grow back.  As hair generally grows on a 6 week cycle, we recommend that all clients come in once every four weeks for the first three months to try and allow the hair to be on the same growth cycle.\n\n- hair can be removed at 1/8? – only 7-10 days of growing (half the length needed for waxing).\n- any pigment or type of hair can be sugared.\n- safe for sensitive skin types.\n- removes ONLY dead skin along with unwanted hair.\n- regular extraction at an  1/8? (the Anagen Phase of hair growth)  leads to permanent hair loss. When hair is extracted at that length it pulls some of the follicle wall out with it each time eventually causing it to collapse.\n- does not need to be heated like wax so it will NEVER burn you!\n- hair is removed in the natural direction of growth which eliminates breakage, unnecessary discomfort, irritation and ingrown hairs.\n- eco-friendly and biodegradable.\n- sanitary and individually portioned- no chance of double dipping sticks!\n\n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"\n\nNOTE:  As this is a \"FreeToBe\" listing, please check in with us prior to visiting, to avoid any disappointments.  Phone is good.  In-person is better.', 1, '2022-01-25', '2022-01-25', 1, '2022-01-25 18:41:32', '2022-01-25 18:41:32', 0, ''),
