(639, 31, '1037', '', 'Homeopathy starts here', 'We\'re here to help!\n\nAt Macgregor Homeopathic Medicine, our mission is to create a space for everyone to feel welcome and heard.\n\nOur vision is to have a successful family practice available to all that are appropriate for homeopathy, from treating the young - who are just beginning the journey of life, to elders who have so much to share.\n\n\nMore About Nigel\n\nNigel C. MacGregor was born in Vernon, British Columbia in 1994, on one of the hottest days of the year (47 degrees celsius). Growing up on the beach running around in the apple orchards, hiking dessert canyons. Then progressing to the flat fields of St. Albert, Alberta in 2003. After many year battling out on the football fields, 2012 Nigel played in the Canadian Junior Football league (CJFL) for the Edmonton Huskies as an offensive tackle. After 3 years of playing high intensity ball, he knew his body would not keep up with the high impact sport much longer. After discovering the power of homeopathy to help speed up his recovery from physical activity, Nigel decided to learn more about the mysteries of homeopathy.\n\nNigel enrolled at the Canadian College of Homeopathic Medicine (CCHM) in 2017 and by June 2019 he finished the intensive 3-year course and graduated late June 2019. By July 2019, Nigel applied to the College of Homeopaths of Ontario (CHO) to become a regulated health professional, opening up his own practice, based in Uxbridge, Ontario.\n\nMacGregor Homeopathic Medicine is located in Uxbridge, Ontario at 58 Brock St. W. (suite 201) and shares space with Holly Morris Holistic Wellness.\n\nAt Macgregor Homeopathic Medicine, Nigel created a space for everyone to feel welcome and heard. His vision is to have a successful family practice available to all that are appropriate for homeopathy, from treating the young who are just beginning the journey of life, to our elders who have so much to share. \n', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"\n\nN