(656, 31, '1055', '', 'Achieve the hair of your dreams.', 'Jen Hall’s passion for hairstyling began in her preteens when she’d use her artistic intuition and skill to experiment and express her own personal style. From an even earlier age, visual arts became the foundation for her knowledge and fascination in colour theory.\n\nJen began her career in hairstyling in 2010 in beauty school (Career School of Hairstyling) where she studied L’Oréal Professional. Though formal education had concluded that year, continuing education remains top priority for Jen to advance her skills and stay passionate within her craft.\n \nEach year, Jen continues to invest thousands of dollars and countless hours into education to avoid becoming complacent in an ever-evolving industry. She has trained with impressive leaders and icons in her field - traveling locally and abroad to participate in technical & theory classes in both colour and cut. To stay relevant in our social world, Jen has also taken courses on photography, marketing, and business.\n\nAs with all beauty professionals, Jen\'s career started as an assistant - at Lattitudes Salon & Spa; Jen watched her peers carefully; studying positions and elevations, foiling placements, and dialogue. Her first experience with continuing education began at the MySpace Academy in Markham for a 5 week program. Jen was promoted twice in a six month span after demonstrating significant understanding and ability to provide exceedingly exceptional service at each level. \n\nIn 2012, Jen sought to leave the large, corporate salon environment to begin working for a smaller shop located in downtown Whitby, Axxess Hair Design, where she spent 5 years growing and learning while also participating in two professional hair photo shoots with her team and advanced L’Oreal education. Jen favoured the quiet and intimate atmosphere of the small business & found herself more freedom to develop as an individual stylist. \n\nAfter giving birth to her son, Jack, Jen became acutely aware of the challenges she would face as a stylist and employee with a young child. It was then that she decided to begin her journey working independently.  After 4 years operating two different hair studios within her homes, Jen is so pleased to welcome you to Trulls Rd, Courtice; an intimate & clean space she has curated to reflect her personal style while additionally combining functionality, minimalism, and comfort for her valued guests. Enter her bright, ground level studio through a separate side entrance door and enjoy the beauty and comfort of her Scandinavian style decor.\n\n?Whether you’re a new or existing guest, you can rest assured that Jen’s objective is to achieve your complete satisfaction; with hair that’s thoughtfully executed and personalized to you. Specializing in dimensional hair colour, flawless blends and tonal corrections, Jen not only prioritizes quality but also places great emphasis on healthy hair - the foundation of beautiful hair colour. ', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"\n\nNOTE:  As this is a \"FreeToBe\" listing, please check in with us prior to visiting, to avoid any disappointments.  Phone is good.  In-person is better.', 1, '2022-01-25', '2022-01-25', 1, '2022-01-25 18:34:49', '2022-01-25 18:34:49', 0, ''),
(657, 31, '1069', '', 'Feel limitless!', 'HOW IT STARTED : MY STORY\n\nMy journey into the natural health space began after a motor vehicle accident when I was 16 years old. The damage from that accident left me unable to fully function for more than two years. During that time the only “solutions” offered to me were prescription medications and time. This was the first of many experiences that helped open my eyes to a healthcare system that did not sit well with me. A system that I am thankful for when emergencies strike but one that was based on a “drug it or cut it” mentality that I refused to be a part of. \n\nSo I began studying the body and its incredible abilities to heal itself when given the proper guidance and tools. I enrolled in Massage Therapy college, Holistic Nutrition school, and countless other courses and certifications that focused on a holistic (whole body, mind, spirit) and natural approach to wellness. One that appreciated and celebrated our uniqueness and frowned upon a one-size-fits-all scenario. \n\nWithin that education and throughout the last 20 years within the health and fitness space, I have cultivated the deepest respect for the human body and all that it does to help protect us every second of our lives.\n\nAs the years went by I experienced debilitating digestive issues, breast implant illness, hyperthyroidism, fibromyalgia, depression, parasitic infections, and a laundry list of other nasty health issues. With each departure from wellness I used my Holistic Health and Natural Medicine skills to help bring my own body back into balance. \n\nI have led and supported hundreds of other naturally focused humans to epic levels of wellness using an approach and mindset that ANYTHING and EVERYTHING is fixable, if given the time, opportunity, and care the body needs. I am looking forward to seeing if you and I can also create some magic together, so that you can feel better than ever. ', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"\n\nNOTE:  As this