(740, 5, '1149', '', 'Willkommen!', 'Familiar Land\n\nCrowsfoot Smokehaus is located in the small farming town of Conestogo and stands on what is known to be one of the oldest venues in the region. Settled by Mennonites and German immigrants in the 1820s, the site has had a centuries-long tradition of serving great food in a comfortable and welcoming atmosphere.\n\nThis land has fed families for generations. It\'s where we\'ve laid roots. It\'s where we\'ve laid ground, and where we\'ve laid out dinner. Yes, this land has exchanged hands over the years—it\'s been a tavern, a hotel, a community centre—but it\'s always been a place to gather, to settle, to exchange. And while we\'re not exchanging cattle, horses, and tracts of land anymore, we still come together. To share memories, conversation, and a quality meal.?\n\n\nInspired by the Fire\n\nThe storied traditions of this building span centuries, and live on to this day. They\'ve survived generation after generation; they couldn’t even be extinguished by the fire of 1968, when 127 years of history burnt down in two hours. So we took what they gave us, and we built on it.\n\nOur selection of barbecued meats and vegetables are smoked right here on site by way of our two Oyler Barbecue Pit 1300 smokers, which we imported directly from Mesquite, Texas. Widely considered to be the best smoker in the world, these massive barbecue pits are responsible for creating the rich, smokey flavours you\'ll find throughout our menu.\n\nMaybe it was that catastrophic fire and the rebuilding that followed that gave us inspiration. Maybe it\'s the hospitality that has flowed through these doors for over a century. Either way, at Crowsfoot you\'ll find the warm welcome you\'ve come to expect from this community, and a few new traditions you\'ll be happy to make your own.\n\n\nWillkommen!\n\nWe take pride in honouring a rich history of Mennonites and German immigrants, who settled on this land nearly 200 years ago and called it home.\n\nAs we open these doors once more, we invite you back to something familiar, but new. Something that supports the farmers and neighbours you already know, with a locally-sourced menu that combines the community\'s rich German culture with classic southern-style smokehouse barbecue.\n\nWhether you\'re after a perfectly smoked brisket fresh from the barbecue pit, a hearty helping of our house-made schnitzel or spätzle, or a freshly poured local craft beer from one of our 24 draft taps, there\'s something for everyone to enjoy at Crowsfoot.\n\nAs they say in Germany, Guten Appetit!', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"', 1, '2021-11-11', '2021-11-11', 1, '2021-11-11 12:18:29', '2021-11-11 12:18:29', 0, ''),
(741, 31, '1155', '', 'Kitsilano\'s lower east side snug', 'Kitsilano\'s lower east side snug offers an organic menu for dinner. Our restaurant offers great events Monday to Wednesday.\n\nAt Corduroy, we take great pride to ensure everyone always has a great time, good food and exceptional service. We treat everyone like family and create menu items we know you\'ll love. Chef Figg creates an organic menu for you to appreciate, and always provide innovative weekend specials using local ingredients.\n\nOur nightly events make Corduroy one of the most enjoyable places to visit.\n\nMondays - Rock, Paper, Scissors hosted by Scott Patey and Jolly Brain Productions\nTuesday - Open Mic night with Michael Averill starts at 7pm\nWednesday - Comedy night hosted by Maddy Kelly\nThursday - Dinner and Drink Specials\nFriday - TGIF - Weekend Specials Start at 4:00\nSaturday - it\'s Saturday, need we say more??\nSunday - Sunday Funday - Ask about our Double Caesars', 'Be sure to tell us \"Dux sent me!\"\n\nNOTE:  As this is a \"FreeToBe\" listing, please check in with us prior to visiting, to avoid any disappointments.  Phone is good.  In-person is better.', 1, '2022-01-25', '2022-01-25', 1, '2022-01-25 18:42:29', '2022-01-25 18:42:29', 0, ''),
